FBIS4-15484 "drsov068_a_94035" FBIS-SOV-94-068 Daily Report 8 Apr 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS No Policy Change After Hosokawa's Resignation No Policy Change After Hosokawa's Resignation LD0804103594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0837 GMT 8 Apr 94 LD0804103594 Moscow ITAR-TASS English BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vladimir Solntsev] [Text] Moscow April 8 ITAR-TASS -- The resignation of the Japanese Prime Minister Morihiro Hosokawa is Japan's internal affair. The Moscow policy of developing comprehensive relations with Japan remains unchanged, a ranking official of the Russian Ministry of Foreign Affairs told ITAR-TASS today. He stressed that these relations will continue to develop on the basis of the Tokyo declaration signed after the Russo-Japanese summit last October. The Tokyo declaration outlined the strategic perspective for the development of all-round ties between the two countries.
